quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,175,"And indeed, your Lord - He is the Exalted in Might, the Merciful."
  26,176,"The companions of the thicket [i.e., the people of Madyan] denied the messengers"
  26,177,"When Shuʿayb said to them, "
  33,28,"O Prophet, say to your wives, "
  33,29,"But if you should desire Allāh and His Messenger and the home of the Hereafter - then indeed, Allāh has prepared for the doers of good among you a great reward."
  33,30,"O wives of the Prophet, whoever of you should commit a clear immorality - for her the punishment would be doubled two fold, and ever is that, for Allāh, easy."
  34,7,"But those who disbelieve say, "
  34,8,"Has he invented about Allāh a lie or is there in him madness?"
  34,9,"Then, do they not look at what is before them and what is behind them of the heaven and earth? If We should will, We could cause the earth to swallow them or [could] let fall upon them fragments from the sky. Indeed in that is a sign for every servant turning back [to Allāh]."